<FlowDocument xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
              xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
              Foreground="#E0E0E0"
              Background="#1E1F22"
              FontFamily="Segoe UI"
              FontSize="14"
              PagePadding="32,24,32,24">

    <Paragraph FontSize="28" FontWeight="Bold" Foreground="#FFD700" Margin="0,0,0,4">
        Create Bonus Points Event Point
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Foreground="#A0A0A0" FontSize="13" Margin="0,0,0,16">
        Awards bonus points and displays a message when a special mission condition, sub-mission, or optional objective is completed.
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer>
        <Border Height="1" Background="#444" Margin="0,0,0,12"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,4,0,4">
        What Create Bonus Points Does
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        The <Bold>Create Bonus Points</Bold> Event Point is used to award bonus points to the player
        when they complete a sub-mission, side objective, special condition, or optional mission task.
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="0,6,0,0">
        In practice, the point total does not appear to be meaningfully tallied throughout the game.
        Even so, this Event Point is still useful because it acts as a clean marker that something
        optional or noteworthy has been completed. It can also display confirmation text to the
        player when the Event Point fires.
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,8">
        <Image Source="pack://application:,,,/UrbanChaosMissionEditor;component/Help/Images/mission_bonus_points_overview.png"
               MaxWidth="720" Stretch="Uniform"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,8,0,8">
        <Border Background="#2A2F3A" BorderBrush="#4A5A7A" BorderThickness="1"
                CornerRadius="4" Padding="12">
            <TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap" Foreground="#AFC8FF">
                <Run FontWeight="Bold">Practical use:</Run>
                <Run>
                    Treat Bonus Points as a visible success marker for optional mission actions.
                    The on-screen display text is usually more important than the actual point value.
                </Run>
            </TextBlock>
        </Border>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <BlockUIContainer>
        <Border Height="1" Background="#444" Margin="0,14,0,12"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,0,0,4">
        Adding a Bonus Points Event Point
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        To add this Event Point, click <Bold>Add</Bold> in the Event Points panel, select
        <Bold>Bonus Points</Bold> from the Event Point type list, and click <Bold>OK</Bold>.
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="0,6,0,0">
        The <Bold>Edit EventPoint</Bold> window opens with the normal common properties, trigger
        settings, and the Bonus Points-specific fields.
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,8">
        <Image Source="pack://application:,,,/UrbanChaosMissionEditor;component/Help/Images/mission_bonus_points_add_type.png"
               MaxWidth="720" Stretch="Uniform"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,12,0,4">
        Common Properties
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        Like other Event Points, Bonus Points has common properties such as index number, type,
        letter group, colour, and position. The index and Event Point type are automatic.
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="0,6,0,0">
        Choose a letter group and colour that fits your mission organisation. For example, you might
        keep optional rewards in their own colour or group so they are easy to identify later.
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,8">
        <Image Source="pack://application:,,,/UrbanChaosMissionEditor;component/Help/Images/mission_bonus_points_common_properties.png"
               MaxWidth="720" Stretch="Uniform"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <BlockUIContainer>
        <Border Height="1" Background="#444" Margin="0,14,0,12"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,0,0,4">
        Bonus Points Properties
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        The Bonus Points-specific fields define what kind of bonus is being awarded, how many points
        are awarded, which translation gender value is used, and what text is displayed to the
        player.
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,8">
        <Image Source="pack://application:,,,/UrbanChaosMissionEditor;component/Help/Images/mission_bonus_points_properties.png"
               MaxWidth="720" Stretch="Uniform"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="18" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#9FE3A6" Margin="0,10,0,4">
        Type
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        The <Bold>Type</Bold> field appears to classify what kind of objective the bonus relates to.
        The available values are:
    </Paragraph>

    <List MarkerStyle="Disc" Margin="16,2,0,0">
        <ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Primary</Bold> — likely intended for a main objective or core mission task.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Secondary</Bold> — likely intended for a secondary objective.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Bonus</Bold> — likely intended for side missions, optional tasks, or special rewards.</Paragraph></ListItem>
    </List>

    <Paragraph Margin="0,6,0,0">
        The selected Type does not appear to have a strong gameplay effect. It is probably used more
        for classification than mission logic. Choose the value that best describes the task being
        rewarded.
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontSize="18" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#9FE3A6" Margin="0,10,0,4">
        Points
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        The <Bold>Points</Bold> field is the number of bonus points awarded to the player. The usable
        range is typically <Bold>0–1000</Bold>.
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="0,6,0,0">
        Since the points do not appear to be meaningfully tallied through the game, the exact number
        is mostly a design choice. Use whatever value makes sense for the importance of the optional
        task.
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontSize="18" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#9FE3A6" Margin="0,10,0,4">
        Translation Gender
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        The <Bold>Translation Gender</Bold> value appears to support translated versions of the game,
        such as languages that use masculine and feminine forms for some words.
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="0,6,0,0">
        Setting this value likely tells the game which text variant to display in translated builds.
        In English, this may not make any visible difference. In translated versions, the text system
        may already handle much of this through translation data, so the exact practical effect is
        uncertain.
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontSize="18" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#9FE3A6" Margin="0,10,0,4">
        Display Text
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        <Bold>Display Text</Bold> is the text shown when the Bonus Points Event Point fires. This is
        often the most useful part of the Event Point, because it gives the player immediate feedback
        that they completed an optional task.
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="0,6,0,0">
        Example display text:
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,8">
        <Border Background="#25272B" BorderBrush="#444" BorderThickness="1"
                CornerRadius="4" Padding="10">
            <TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap" Foreground="#E0E0E0" FontFamily="Consolas">
You arrested them!
            </TextBlock>
        </Border>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <BlockUIContainer>
        <Border Height="1" Background="#444" Margin="0,14,0,12"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,0,0,4">
        Trigger Settings
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        Bonus Points does not normally fire by itself. It should be placed behind a trigger that
        represents the bonus condition being completed.
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="0,6,0,0">
        For example, if the bonus should be awarded when a specific NPC is arrested, set:
    </Paragraph>

    <List MarkerStyle="Disc" Margin="16,2,0,0">
        <ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Triggered By:</Bold> Person Arrested.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Listening Mode:</Bold> Active.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Target EP:</Bold> the Event Point number of the NPC that must be arrested.</Paragraph></ListItem>
    </List>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,8,0,8">
        <Border Background="#4A2424" BorderBrush="#C45A5A" BorderThickness="2"
                CornerRadius="4" Padding="14">
            <TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap" Foreground="#FFD0D0" FontSize="15">
                <Run FontWeight="Bold">Critical Target EP detail:</Run>
                <Run>
                    If the trigger checks a specific person, Target EP must point to that person’s Event Point number.
                    For a Person Arrested trigger, Target EP should be the NPC Event Point that must be arrested.
                    If Target EP is wrong, the bonus may not trigger when expected.
                </Run>
            </TextBlock>
        </Border>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,8">
        <Image Source="pack://application:,,,/UrbanChaosMissionEditor;component/Help/Images/mission_bonus_points_trigger_settings.png"
               MaxWidth="720" Stretch="Uniform"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <BlockUIContainer>
        <Border Height="1" Background="#444" Margin="0,14,0,12"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,0,0,4">
        Example: Award Bonus Points When an NPC Is Arrested
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        This example awards a small bonus when the player arrests a specific NPC.
    </Paragraph>

    <List MarkerStyle="Decimal" Margin="16,2,0,0">
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Create or select the NPC that must be arrested.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Note that NPC’s Event Point number from the Event Points list.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Create a <Bold>Bonus Points</Bold> Event Point.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Set <Bold>Type</Bold> to <Bold>Primary</Bold>.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Set <Bold>Points</Bold> to <Bold>10</Bold>.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Set <Bold>Translation Gender</Bold> to <Bold>Male</Bold>.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Set <Bold>Display Text</Bold> to <Bold>You arrested them!</Bold>.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Set <Bold>Triggered By</Bold> to <Bold>Person Arrested</Bold>.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Set <Bold>Listening Mode</Bold> to <Bold>Active</Bold>.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Set <Bold>Target EP</Bold> to the Event Point number of the NPC that must be arrested.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Click <Bold>OK</Bold>, save the mission, and test it in game.</Paragraph></ListItem>
    </List>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,8">
        <Image Source="pack://application:,,,/UrbanChaosMissionEditor;component/Help/Images/mission_bonus_points_example_arrest.png"
               MaxWidth="720" Stretch="Uniform"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph>
        When the target NPC is arrested, the Bonus Points Event Point should fire and display the
        configured text.
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,12,0,4">
        Basic Bonus Points Workflow
    </Paragraph>
    <List MarkerStyle="Decimal" Margin="16,2,0,0">
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Decide what optional task or sub-mission should award the bonus.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Create the Event Point or NPC that represents the completion condition.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Note any required target Event Point number.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Add a <Bold>Bonus Points</Bold> Event Point.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Set Type, Points, Translation Gender, and Display Text.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Set the trigger that represents the condition being completed.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>If the trigger needs a target, set <Bold>Target EP</Bold> correctly.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Save and test the mission.</Paragraph></ListItem>
    </List>

</FlowDocument>